div1.p: In the District Court of the third Judicial District of Washington Territory holding terms at Seattle
In the matter of the application of W.C. Hutchinson for writ of Habeas Corpus} No. H7011 Order

The above named cause coming on before me upon motion of the petitioner Hutchinson through his attorneys Pasint Gilman & Jas H Lewis for release, and upon investigation et appearing to me that the said Hutchinson was illegally restrained of his libery by one W.S.C.Harris, and that the said Harris had no legal authority for such restraint therfore be it adjudged & ordered, that the said Harris release the said Hutchinson, & permit him to go free, and that the said Harris have judgment entered up against him for the cost amounting to 114.90of this action and attorneys fee of $10 as allowed by law, and that judgment enter
against him for the amount and execution issue there for
Paled at House W.T. 13th November A.D. 1885} Gueni, Judge
In re Application of C.W. Hutchinson for a Writ of Habeas Corpus
FILED NOV 13 1885 James Seavey, Clerk By James P. Ludlow
Jas Hamilton Lewis Atty for Petitioner
